article.headline: Indiana St. 76, Wis.-Milwaukee 63
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. -- Rashad Reed scored 16 points to help Indiana State defeat Wisconsin-Milwaukee 76-63 on Tuesday. Reed made six field goals, including four 3-pointers, in a consolation round game of the Dick's Sporting Goods NIT Season Tipoff. Leading 46-45, the Sycamores went on an 18-9 run as Reed made three of his 3-pointers. He also added a two-point basket as the Sycamores went on top 64-54. Dwayne Lathan, who came off the bench, made all seven of his field goal attempts and scored 14 points for Indiana State (2-1). Harry Marshall and Jake Kelly had 11 points each for the Sycamores. Milwaukee (1-2) took a 12-3 lead, but trailed 38-36 at halftime. The Panthers made 26 percent (10-for-39) of their second-half shots from the field. Deonte Roberts led Milwaukee with 13 points. James Eayrs added 10 points and 10 rebounds for the Panthers, but missed 14 of his 18 field goal attempts.
